<DefaultLayout title="Attacker Perspective">
  <PageHeader
      title="Attacker Perspective"
      subtitle="In the world where we spend most of our time, our students are surrounded by people they can trust - their closest ones - parents, family members, such as sisters or brothers, and friends of the same age. When they go to school or attend clubs, their circle of people expands to include classmates, teachers, and teaching assistants. When your students go to and from school, they see other people and get to know those around them, such as ice cream vendors, bus drivers, peers from parallel classes, or even older children. Thus, adversaries with bad intentions might use someone that your students know, pretend and give expert suggestions to gain trust and later to manipulate them. It is important for your student to understand, identify and ask for help."
      bgType="bordered"
  />

